# Chaos Stability Analyst â€” tabled results

| Item | Content |
|---|---|
| Stable chaos (definition) | For \(N\) particles under Boltzmannâ€“Grad scaling, say chaos is stable if \(\mathbb H_N(t)=\mathrm{Ent}(F_N(t)\,|\,\prod_{i=1}^N M_{\rho(t,x_i),u(t,x_i),\theta(t,x_i)})\le C(\mathbb H_N(0)+N\varepsilon^\gamma)\) for all \(t\in[0,T]\), fixed \(T>0\), some \(\gamma>0\). |
