## 1. Why the **Lanford â†’ Boltzmann â†’ NS bridge for *all times*** matters so much

Right now, hereâ€™s the situation:  

| Link | Whatâ€™s proven today | Restriction |
|------|---------------------|-------------|
| **Particles â†’ Boltzmann equation** (Lanfordâ€™s theorem, 1974) | For dilute gases, as \(N\to\infty\) with Boltzmannâ€“Grad scaling, the empirical distribution converges to the Boltzmann equation. | Valid only for *very short times* (comparable to mean free path). Past that, recollisions ruin control. |
