## Mini-proof that O1â€² â‡’ O3â€² (the essential stitch)

| Line | Content |
|---|---|
| Decompose \(f=Pf+\Pi f\) | \(P\) projects onto invariants; only \(\Pi f\) is dissipated by \(L\). |
| Microscopic dissipation (O1â€²) | \(-\langle Lf,f\rangle\ge \lambda_{\text{coll}}\|\Pi f\|_{\nu,M}^2\). |
| Add transport via a mixed energy | \(\mathcal E=\|f\|_{L^2_M}^2+\eta_1\langle\nabla_x f,\nabla_v f\rangle_M+\eta_2\|\nabla_x f\|_{L^2_M}^2+\beta\|Pf\|_{H^1_x}^2\). |
| Differentiate \(\mathcal E\) along solutions | Transport cancels in \(\|f\|^2\), but the mixed term converts it into \(-\|\nabla_x f\|^2\); combine with O1â€² and PoincarÃ© on \(Pf\). |
| Close small nonlinear term | Near equilibrium (O2) absorbs \(Q(f,f)\) by Youngâ€™s inequality. |
| Conclusion (O3â€²) | \(\dot{\mathcal E}\le -\mu\,\mathcal E\Rightarrow \mathcal E(t)\le \mathcal E(0)e^{-\mu t}\). |

