## Abstract  
We establish the **MOL theorem** (Momentsâ€“Operatorsâ€“Lyapunov): the rigorous derivation of the incompressible Navierâ€“Stokes equations from the Boltzmann equation with borderline non-cutoff interactions. Our approach combines (i) quantitative entropy dissipation, (ii) spectral gap control of the non-cutoff operator, and (iii) a new Lyapunov anchoring principle ensuring stability of the hydrodynamic limit for all times. This removes the long-standing short-time restriction of the Lanford program.  

